    • draw

      public void draw(Graphics2D graphics2D, GamePanel gamePanel)

      draw

      Draws the object on the screen if it is within the camera frame.
      Parameters:
      graphics2D - the graphics context used for drawing
      gamePanel - the game panel containing the object and the hero

    • isInCameraFrame

      private boolean isInCameraFrame(int blockSize, int heroWorldX, int heroScreenX, int heroWorldY, int heroScreenY)

      isInCameraFrame

      Checks if the object is within the camera frame.
      Parameters:
      blockSize - the size of a block (tile)
      heroWorldX - the X position of the hero in the world
      heroScreenX - the X position of the hero on the screen
      heroWorldY - the Y position of the hero in the world
      heroScreenY - the Y position of the hero on the screen
      Returns:
      true if the object is within the camera frame, false otherwise
